Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown; grey core. Rectangular stamp with egg-and-dart motif.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 80, 48. Compare Calvet, Salamine de Chypre III, Les timbres amphoriques, no.130 and P. Dupont, 'Timbres amphoriques de la Grece archaique', in N. Badoud and A, Marangou (eds), Analyse et exploitation des timbres amphoriques grecques (Rennes 2019) 38 (example from Berezan, but not with omicron, as suggested).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1528)
